                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract9-1">
                        <quote source="#bib9-1">Bp. of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/182">Seleucia-Ctesiphon</placeName> and martyr. Shemʿon was probably the immediate 
                            successor of Papa bar ʿAggai (d. between 327 and 335), but nothing is known about his tenure as bp. prior to his arrest.</quote></note>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="description">In hagiography: <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/9">Simeon bar Sabbaʿe</persName> is commemorated 
                        as bishop of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/182">Seleucia-Ctesiphon</placeName> and one of the earliest and most famous of 
                        the Persian Martyrs. He was from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/415">Susa</placeName> and was the archdeacon of Catholicos Papa 
                        bar ʿAggai whom he succeeded in 329. He was imprisoned at Karka d-Ledan and was decapitated.</note>
